<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:fileTags="Tags/okta-authors.Kimli Welsh">
    <body>
        <p>After you set up Okta as the identity provider to <MadCap:variable name="Mobile.VIDM" />, add the newly-created authentication method to access policies in <MadCap:variable name="Mobile.VIDM" />. Update the default access policy, and other policies as needed.</p>
        <p>You need to add the Okta authentication method to the default access policy so that Okta is used as the sign in provider for the <MadCap:variable name="Mobile.WS1" /> catalog. The default access policy governs login to the catalog and any apps configured in <MadCap:variable name="Mobile.VIDM" /> that do not have another policy definition already.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>In the  <MadCap:variable name="Mobile.VIDM" /> console, click the Identity &amp; Access Management tab, then click <span class="uicontrol">Policies</span>.</li>
            <li>Click <span class="uicontrol">Edit Default Access Policy</span>.</li>
            <li>In the Edit Policy wizard, click <span class="uicontrol">Configuration</span>.</li>
            <li>Click the policy rule for Web browsers.</li>
            <ul> <li>
                Set Okta authentication as the authentication method.
            </li><p>If the user's network range is <span class="uicontrol">ALL RANGES</span>, the user is accessing content from <span class="uicontrol">Web Browser</span>, and the user belongs to <span class="uicontrol">Empty (all users)</span>&#160;group, perform this action: <span class="uicontrol">Authenticate using . . .</span>. The end user may authenticate using: <span class="uicontrol">Okta Auth Method</span>.</p><p>For <span class="uicontrol">Okta Auth Method</span>, select the authentication method you created for the IDP in <MadCap:xref href="../SAML/Desktop/configure-okta-idp-vidm-desktop.htm#complete-create-new-idp">Complete creating a new Identity Provider in [%=Mobile.VIDM%]</MadCap:xref></p><p>For <span class="uicontrol">Okta Auth Method</span>, select the authentication method you created for the IDP in <MadCap:xref href="../SAML/Desktop/configure-okta-idp-vidm-desktop.htm#complete-create-new-idp">Complete creating a new Identity Provider in [%=Mobile.VIDM%]</MadCap:xref></p><li>Click <span class="uicontrol">Save</span>.</li></ul>
            <li>Edit other policies as needed to add the Okta authentication method.
				</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>